"from\": 4093, \"to\": 4105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The omnium is a collection of four different events, all held on the same day.\", \"from\": 4110, \"to\": 4188, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The omnium\", \"from\": 4110, \"to\": 4120}, {\"ngram\": \"a collection\", \"from\": 4124, \"to\": 4136}, {\"ngram\": \"four different events\", \"from\": 4140, \"to\": 4161}, {\"ngram\": \"the same day\", \"from\": 4175, \"to\": 4187}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first event is the scratch race, with a first-past-the-post race over 10km for men and 7.5km for women.\", \"from\": 4190, \"to\": 4297, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The first event\", \"from\": 4190, \"to\": 4205}, {\"ngram\": \"the scratch race\", \"from\": 4209, \"to\": 4225}, {\"ngram\": \"the-post\", \"from\": 4245, \"to\": 4253}, {\"ngram\": \"over 10km\", \"from\": 4259, \"to\": 4268}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 4273, \"to\": 4276}, {\"ngram\": \"7.5km\", \"from\": 4281, \"to\": 4286}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4291, \"to\": 4296}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's followed by the tempo race, where points are awarded for sprints and for lapping the field.\", \"from\": 4299, \"to\": 4397, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the tempo race\", \"from\": 4318, \"to\": 4332}, {\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 4340, \"to\": 4346}, {\"ngram\": \"sprints\", \"from\": 4363, \"to\": 4370}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 4387, \"to\": 4396}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After four laps, there is a sprint every lap, but making a breakaway and lapping the field will garner many more points than winning a sprint.\", \"from\": 4398, \"to\": 4540, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"four laps\", \"from\": 4404, \"to\": 4413}, {\"ngram\": \"a sprint\", \"from\": 4424, \"to\": 4432}, {\"ngram\": \"every lap\", \"from\": 4433, \"to\": 4442}, {\"ngram\": \"a breakaway\", \"from\": 4455, \"to\": 4466}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 4479, \"to\": 4488}, {\"ngram\": \"many more points\", \"from\": 4501, \"to\": 4517}, {\"ngram\": \"a sprint\", \"from\": 4531, \"to\": 4539}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Next is the elimination race, with a sprint taking place every other lap, and the last rider eliminated each time.\", \"from\": 4542, \"to\": 4656, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the elimination race\", \"from\": 4550, \"to\": 4570}, {\"ngram\": \"a sprint\", \"from\": 4577, \"to\": 4585}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 4593, \"to\": 4598}, {\"ngram\": \"every other lap\", \"from\": 4599, \"to\": 4614}, {\"ngram\": \"the last rider\", \"from\": 4620, \"to\": 4634}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, the points race is over 100 laps (25km) for men and 80 laps (20km) for women.\", \"from\": 4658, \"to\": 4744, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the points race\", \"from\": 4667, \"to\": 4682}, {\"ngram\": \"over 100 laps\", \"from\": 4686, \"to\": 4699}, {\"ngram\": \"25km\", \"from\": 4701, \"to\": 4705}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 4711, \"to\": 4714}, {\"ngram\": \"80 laps\", \"from\": 4719, \"to\": 4726}, {\"ngram\": \"20km\", \"from\": 4728, \"to\": 4732}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4738, \"to\": 4743}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a sprint every 10 laps and, as with the tempo race, there is a large benefit from lapping the field.\", \"from\": 4745, \"to\": 4854, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a sprint\", \"from\": 4754, \"to\": 4762}, {\"ngram\": \"every 10 laps\", \"from\": 4763, \"to\": 4776}, {\"ngram\": \"the tempo race\", \"from\": 4790, \"to\": 4804}, {\"ngram\": \"a large benefit\", \"from\": 4815, \"to\": 4830}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 4844, \"to\": 4853}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Readwhat is the omniumfor more details.\", \"from\": 4856, \"to\": 4895, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Readwhat\", \"from\": 4856, \"to\": 4864}, {\"ngram\": \"the omniumfor\", \"from\": 4868, \"to\": 4881}, {\"ngram\": \"more details\", \"from\": 4882, \"to\": 4894}]}, {\"sentence\": \"https://www.gettyimages.co.uk/detail/news-photo/benjamin-thomas-of-team-france-sprints-during-the-mens-news-photo/1332821181?adppopup=true The final Olympic track cycling event is the madison.\", \"from\": 4897, \"to\": 5092, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The final Olympic track cycling event\", \"from\": 5036, \"to\": 5073}, {\"ngram\": \"the madison\", \"from\": 5077, \"to\": 5088}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a mass-start event with 16 teams of two on the track at a time and relies on points to determine the winner.\", \"from\": 5093, \"to\": 5206, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a mass-start event\", \"from\": 5098, \"to\": 5116}, {\"ngram\": \"16 teams\", \"from\": 5122, \"to\": 5130}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 5141, \"to\": 5150}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 5154, \"to\": 5160}, {\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 5175, \"to\": 5181}, {\"ngram\": \"the winner\", \"from\": 5195, \"to\": 5205}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Points are accrued via sprints throughout the race and by lapping the field.\", \"from\": 5207, \"to\": 5283, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Points\", \"from\": 5207, \"to\": 5213}, {\"ngram\": \"sprints\", \"from\": 5230, \"to\": 5237}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 5249, \"to\": 5257}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 5273, \"to\": 5282}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's race takes place over 200 laps (50km), while the women race over 120 laps (30km).\", \"from\": 5284, \"to\": 5375, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The men's race\", \"from\": 5284, \"to\": 5298}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 5305, \"to\": 5310}, {\"ngram\": \"200 laps\", \"from\": 5316, \"to\": 5324}, {\"ngram\": \"50km\", \"from\": 5326, \"to\": 5330}, {\"ngram\": \"the women\", \"from\": 5339, \"to\": 5348}, {\"ngram\": \"over 120 laps\", \"from\": 5354, \"to\": 5367}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only one of the two riders will be active at any time, the other must remain above the blue 'stayer' line until a handover using a handsling to pull the second rider back into competition.\", \"from\": 5377, \"to\": 5565, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the two riders\", \"from\": 5389, \"to\": 5403}, {\"ngram\": \"any time\", \"from\": 5422, \"to\": 5430}, {\"ngram\": \"the blue 'stayer' line\", \"from\": 5460, \"to\": 5482}, {\"ngram\": \"a handover\", \"from\": 5489, \"to\": 5499}, {\"ngram\": \"a handsling\", \"from\": 5506, \"to\": 5517}, {\"ngram\": \"the second rider\", \"from\": 5526, \"to\": 5542}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 5553, \"to\": 5564}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's up to the team to decide the timing of its handover.\", \"from\": 5566, \"to\": 5623, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 5577, \"to\": 5585}, {\"ngram\": \"the timing\", \"from\": 5596, \"to\": 5606}, {\"ngram\": \"its handover\", \"from\": 5610, \"to\": 5622}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Readwhat is the madisonfor more details.\", \"from\": 5625, \"to\": 5665, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Readwhat\", \"from\": 5625, \"to\": 5633}, {\"ngram\": \"the madisonfor\", \"from\": 5637, \"to\": 5651}, {\"ngram\": \"more details\", \"from\": 5652, \"to\": 5664}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Track cyclists ride on a fixed gear bike, which does not have a freewheel in the rear hub.\", \"from\": 5669, \"to\": 5759, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Track cyclists\", \"from\": 5669, \"to\": 5683}, {\"ngram\": \"a fixed gear bike\", \"from\": 5692, \"to\": 5709}, {\"ngram\": \"a freewheel\", \"from\": 5731, \"to\": 5742}, {\"ngram\": \"the rear hub\", \"from\": 5746, \"to\": 5758}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the single sprocket at the rear is attached directly to the rear wheel.\", \"from\": 5760, \"to\": 5840, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the single sprocket\", \"from\": 5769, \"to\": 5788}, {\"ngram\": \"the rear\", \"from\": 5792, \"to\": 5800}, {\"ngram\": \"the rear wheel\", \"from\": 5825, \"to\": 5839}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This allows good power transfer for explosive acceleration, but means that the rider must pedal while the bike is moving.\", \"from\": 5841, \"to\": 5962, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"good power transfer\", \"from\": 5853, \"to\": 5872}, {\"ngram\": \"explosive acceleration\", \"from\": 5877, \"to\": 5899}, {\"ngram\": \"the rider\", \"from\": 5916, \"to\": 5925}, {\"ngram\": \"the bike\", \"from\": 5943, \"to\": 5951}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It also means that braking is via the rider's legs rather than having a mechanical brake.\", \"from\": 5963, \"to\": 6052, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rider's legs\", \"from\": 5997, \"to\": 6013}, {\"ngram\": \"a mechanical brake\", \"from\": 6033, \"to\": 6051}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A derny is a motor-powered bike.\", \"from\": 6056, \"to\": 6088, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A derny\", \"from\": 6056, \"to\": 6063}, {\"ngram\": \"a motor-powered bike\", \"from\": 6067, \"to\": 6087}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Riders ride behind the derny in the first few laps of the keirin event as they gather speed.\", \"from\": 6089, \"to\": 6181, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Riders\", \"from\": 6089, \"to\": 6095}, {\"ngram\": \"the derny\", \"from\": 6108, \"to\": 6117}, {\"ngram\": \"the first few laps\", \"from\": 6121, \"to\": 6139}, {\"ngram\": \"the keirin event\", \"from\": 6143, \"to\": 6159}, {\"ngram\": \"speed\", \"from\": 6175, \"to\": 6180}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The derny then peels off and the riders compete against each other.\", \"from\": 6182, \"to\": 6249, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The derny\", \"from\": 6182, \"to\": 6191}, {\"ngram\": \"the riders\", \"from\": 6211, \"to\": 6221}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dernys used to be powered by a small petrol motor with a fuel tank over the front wheel, but modern dernys are increasingly powered by an electric motor.\", \"from\": 6251, \"to\": 6404, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dernys\", \"from\": 6251, \"to\": 6257}, {\"ngram\": \"a small petrol motor\", \"from\": 6280, \"to\": 6300}, {\"ngram\": \"a fuel tank\", \"from\": 6306, \"to\": 6317}, {\"ngram\": \"the front wheel\", \"from\": 6323, \"to\": 6338}, {\"ngram\": \"modern dernys\", \"from\": 6344, \"to\": 6357}, {\"ngram\": \"an electric motor\", \"from\": 6386, \"to\": 6403}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The derny rider will sit upright to help lower wind resistance for the riders behind.\", \"from\": 6405, \"to\": 6490, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The derny rider\", \"from\": 6405, \"to\": 6420}, {\"ngram\": \"lower wind resistance\", \"from\": 6446, \"to\": 6467}, {\"ngram\": \"the riders\", \"from\": 6472, \"to\": 6482}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They can travel up to 90km/h, but races rarely exceed 80km/h.\", \"from\": 6492, \"to\": 6553, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"up to 90km/h\", \"from\": 6508, \"to\": 6520}, {\"ngram\": \"races\", \"from\": 6526, \"to\": 6531}, {\"ngram\": \"80km/h\", \"from\": 6546, \"to\": 6552}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A tubular tyre is formed as a continuous roll of casing fabric, like a circular sausage, with the inside edges of the tyre sewn together.\", \"from\": 6555, \"to\": 6692, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A tubular tyre\", \"from\": 6555, \"to\": 6569}, {\"ngram\": \"a continuous roll\", \"from\": 6583, \"to\": 6600}, {\"ngram\": \"casing fabric\", \"from\": 6604, \"to\": 6617}, {\"ngram\": \"a circular sausage\", \"from\": 6624, \"to\": 6642}, {\"ngram\": \"the inside edges\", \"from\": 6649, \"to\": 6665}, {\"ngram\": \"the tyre\", \"from\": 6669, \"to\": 6677}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is an inner tube enclosed in the casing.\", \"from\": 6693, \"to\": 6739, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an inner tube\", \"from\": 6702, \"to\": 6715}, {\"ngram\": \"the casing\", \"from\": 6728, \"to\": 6738}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tyre is glued to the wheel rim, which has a shallow dish rather than the more standard clincher wheel's raised rims.\", \"from\": 6740, \"to\": 6860, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The tyre\", \"from\": 6740, \"to\": 6748}, {\"ngram\": \"the wheel rim\", \"from\": 6761, \"to\": 6774}, {\"ngram\": \"a shallow dish\", \"from\": 6786, \"to\": 6800}, {\"ngram\": \"the more standard clincher wheel's raised rims\", \"from\": 6813, \"to\": 6859}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tubular tyres used to be popular with road racing cyclists, but they have largely been replaced by tubeless clinchers.\", \"from\": 6862, \"to\": 6980, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tubular tyres\", \"from\": 6862, \"to\": 6875}, {\"ngram\": \"road racing cyclists\", \"from\": 6900, \"to\": 6920}, {\"ngram\": \"tubeless clinchers\", \"from\": 6961, \"to\": 6979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are still used on the track due to their ability to hold high pressures, but some nations have begun using tubeless tyres and inner tubes on the track too.\", \"from\": 6981, \"to\": 7141, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 7004, \"to\": 7013}, {\"ngram\": \"their ability\", \"from\": 7021, \"to\": 7034}, {\"ngram\": \"high pressures\", \"from\": 7043, \"to\": 7057}, {\"ngram\": \"some nations\", \"from\": 7063, \"to\": 7075}, {\"ngram\": \"tubeless tyres\", \"from\": 7093, \"to\": 7107}, {\"ngram\": \"inner tubes\", \"from\": 7112, \"to\": 7123}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 7127, \"to\": 7136}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While on roads, wider tyres at lower pressures are faster, a narrow tyre at high pressure is still faster on a track due to the smooth surface.\", \"from\": 7143, \"to\": 7286, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"roads\", \"from\": 7152, \"to\": 7157}, {\"ngram\": \"wider tyres\", \"from\": 7159, \"to\": 7170}, {\"ngram\": \"lower pressures\", \"from\": 7174, \"to\": 7189}, {\"ngram\": \"a narrow tyre\", \"from\": 7202, \"to\": 7215}, {\"ngram\": \"high pressure\", \"from\": 7219, \"to\": 7232}, {\"ngram\": \"a track\", \"from\": 7252, \"to\": 7259}, {\"ngram\": \"the smooth surface\", \"from\": 7267, \"to\": 7285}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thus track bike tyres are typically run at over 100psi, in some cases up to 200psi.\", \"from\": 7287, \"to\": 7370, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"track bike tyres\", \"from\": 7292, \"to\": 7308}, {\"ngram\": \"some cases\", \"from\": 7346, \"to\": 7356}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A disc wheel is a wheel which has enclosed sides, rather than using spokes.\", \"from\": 7372, \"to\": 7447, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A disc wheel\", \"from\": 7372, \"to\": 7384}, {\"ngram\": \"a wheel\", \"from\": 7388, \"to\": 7395}, {\"ngram\": \"sides\", \"from\": 7415, \"to\": 7420}, {\"ngram\": \"spokes\", \"from\": 7440, \"to\": 7446}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's often used as a rear wheel for time trial bikes, due to its aerodynamic qualities, although disc wheels are in general heavier than spoked wheels, as well as more expensive.\", \"from\": 7448, \"to\": 7626, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a rear wheel\", \"from\": 7467, \"to\": 7479}, {\"ngram\": \"time trial bikes\", \"from\": 7484, \"to\": 7500}, {\"ngram\": \"its aerodynamic qualities\", \"from\": 7509, \"to\": 7534}, {\"ngram\": \"disc wheels\", \"from\": 7545, \"to\": 7556}, {\"ngram\": \"spoked wheels\", \"from\": 7585, \"to\": 7598}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's rare for cyclists to use a disc wheel at the front because wind catching it can make it more difficult to steer safely, butWout van Aert did use one in the time trial in Paris.\", \"from\": 7627, \"to\": 7808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7802, \"end\": 7807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.732615023293529e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"cyclists\", \"from\": 7641, \"to\": 7649}, {\"ngram\": \"a disc wheel\", \"from\": 7657, \"to\": 7669}, {\"ngram\": \"the front\", \"from\": 7673, \"to\": 7682}, {\"ngram\": \"wind\", \"from\": 7691, \"to\": 7695}, {\"ngram\": \"butWout van Aert\", \"from\": 7752, \"to\": 7768}, {\"ngram\": \"the time trial\", \"from\": 7784, \"to\": 7798}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indoors, where wind is not an issue, disc wheels are more commonly used at the front as well as at the rear.\", \"from\": 7810, \"to\": 7918, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Indoors\", \"from\": 7810, \"to\": 7817}, {\"ngram\": \"wind\", \"from\": 7825, \"to\": 7829}, {\"ngram\": \"an issue\", \"from\": 7837, \"to\": 7845}, {\"ngram\": \"disc wheels\", \"from\": 7847, \"to\": 7858}, {\"ngram\": \"the front\", \"from\": 7885, \"to\": 7894}, {\"ngram\": \"the rear\", \"from\": 7909, \"to\": 7917}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A trispoke wheel has three wide carbon spokes between its rim and hub.\", \"from\": 7920, \"to\": 7990, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A trispoke wheel\", \"from\": 7920, \"to\": 7936}, {\"ngram\": \"three wide carbon spokes\", \"from\": 7941, \"to\": 7965}, {\"ngram\": \"its rim\", \"from\": 7974, \"to\": 7981}, {\"ngram\": \"hub\", \"from\": 7986, \"to\": 7989}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's more manoeuvrable than a disc wheel, but more aero than a spoked wheel and typically used as the front wheel of a track bike.\", \"from\": 7991, \"to\": 8121, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a disc wheel\", \"from\": 8019, \"to\": 8031}, {\"ngram\": \"more aero\", \"from\": 8037, \"to\": 8046}, {\"ngram\": \"a spoked wheel\", \"from\": 8052, \"to\": 8066}, {\"ngram\": \"the front wheel\", \"from\": 8089, \"to\": 8104}, {\"ngram\": \"a track bike\", \"from\": 8108, \"to\": 8120}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not all track bikes are equipped with front wheels with three spokes; wheels with four or more spokes are also often used.\", \"from\": 8123, \"to\": 8245, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Not all track bikes\", \"from\": 8123, \"to\": 8142}, {\"ngram\": \"front wheels\", \"from\": 8161, \"to\": 8173}, {\"ngram\": \"three spokes\", \"from\": 8179, \"to\": 8191}, {\"ngram\": \"wheels\", \"from\": 8193, \"to\": 8199}, {\"ngram\": \"four or more spokes\", \"from\": 8205, \"to\": 8224}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Track cyclists can achieve peak speeds in sprint and team pursuit events of around 80km/h.\", \"from\": 8247, \"to\": 8337, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Track cyclists\", \"from\": 8247, \"to\": 8261}, {\"ngram\": \"peak speeds\", \"from\": 8274, \"to\": 8285}, {\"ngram\": \"sprint\", \"from\": 8289, \"to\": 8295}, {\"ngram\": \"team\", \"from\": 8300, \"to\": 8304}, {\"ngram\": \"pursuit events\", \"from\": 8305, \"to\": 8319}, {\"ngram\": \"around 80km/h\", \"from\": 8323, \"to\": 8336}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's world record for the team pursuit is 3:42.032, which is an average of almost 65km/h (40.3mph) from a standing start.\", \"from\": 8338, \"to\": 8464, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The men's world record\", \"from\": 8338, \"to\": 8360}, {\"ngram\": \"the team pursuit\", \"from\": 8365, \"to\": 8381}, {\"ngram\": \"an average\", \"from\": 8404, \"to\": 8414}, {\"ngram\": \"40.3mph\", \"from\": 8433, \"to\": 8440}, {\"ngram\": \"a standing start\", \"from\": 8447, \"to\": 8463}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since they are fixed-gear bikes, riders of track bikes can decelerate just by lowering their pedalling cadence, so there is no need for brakes.\", \"from\": 8466, \"to\": 8609, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fixed-gear bikes\", \"from\": 8481, \"to\": 8497}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 8499, \"to\": 8505}, {\"ngram\": \"track bikes\", \"from\": 8509, \"to\": 8520}, {\"ngram\": \"their pedalling cadence\", \"from\": 8553, \"to\": 8576}, {\"ngram\": \"no need\", \"from\": 8590, \"to\": 8597}, {\"ngram\": \"brakes\", \"from\": 8602, \"to\": 8608}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The track is flat and there are no obstacles to prevent a controlled slowing down without braking.\", \"from\": 8610, \"to\": 8708, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The track\", \"from\": 8610, \"to\": 8619}, {\"ngram\": \"no obstacles\", \"from\": 8642, \"to\": 8654}, {\"ngram\": \"a controlled slowing\", \"from\": 8666, \"to\": 8686}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Track cycling and road racing are very different events, requiring different rider capabilities.\", \"from\": 8710, \"to\": 8806, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Track cycling and road racing\", \"from\": 8710, \"to\": 8739}, {\"ngram\": \"very different events\", \"from\": 8744, \"to\": 8765}, {\"ngram\": \"different rider capabilities\", \"from\": 8777, \"to\": 8805}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Tour de France takes place over 3,000km-plus over 21 days of racing.\", \"from\": 8807, \"to\": 8879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8811, \"end\": 8825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.649740716005446e-27, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 8832, \"to\": 8837}, {\"ngram\": \"3,000km\", \"from\": 8843, \"to\": 8850}, {\"ngram\": \"over 21 days\", \"from\": 8856, \"to\": 8868}, {\"ngram\": \"racing\", \"from\": 8872, \"to\": 8878}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In contrast, track events are all under 100km, most significantly so, and some are as short as 200 metres.\", \"from\": 8881, \"to\": 8987, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"contrast\", \"from\": 8884, \"to\": 8892}, {\"ngram\": \"track events\", \"from\": 8894, \"to\": 8906}, {\"ngram\": \"100km\", \"from\": 8921, \"to\": 8926}, {\"ngram\": \"200 metres\", \"from\": 8976, \"to\": 8986}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are on the flat too, so a rider does not need to be good at climbing, unlike Tour de France winners.\", \"from\": 8988, \"to\": 9093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9070, \"end\": 9084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.649740716005446e-27, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the flat\", \"from\": 9000, \"to\": 9008}, {\"ngram\": \"a rider\", \"from\": 9017, \"to\": 9024}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Track cyclists tend to be powerfully built and good at anaerobic exercise, whereas Tour de France winners are lean and have high aerobic capacity.\", \"from\": 9094, \"to\": 9240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9177, \"end\": 9191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.649740716005446e-27, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Track cyclists\", \"from\": 9094, \"to\": 9108}, {\"ngram\": \"anaerobic exercise\", \"from\": 9149, \"to\": 9167}, {\"ngram\": \"high aerobic capacity\", \"from\": 9218, \"to\": 9239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is occasionally some crossover between road and track cyclists though.\", \"from\": 9242, \"to\": 9318, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some crossover\", \"from\": 9264, \"to\": 9278}, {\"ngram\": \"road and track cyclists\", \"from\": 9287, \"to\": 9310}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Filippo Ganna is an Italian road cyclist who races time trials, has raced the Tour de France, and will compete in the Team Pursuit in Paris.\", \"from\": 9319, \"to\": 9459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9319, \"end\": 9332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filippo_Ganna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Filippo Ganna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filippo_Ganna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filippo_Ganna\"}, {\"begin\": 9339, \"end\": 9346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.6133144053445242, \"rank\": 0.6304847910024839, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 9397, \"end\": 9411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.649740716005446e-27, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 9437, \"end\": 9449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.497723828959308e-55, \"text\": \"Team Pursuit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\"}, {\"begin\": 9453, \"end\": 9458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.732615023293529e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"time trials\", \"from\": 9370, \"to\": 9381}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He will almost certainly never win the Tour de France though, as his skill is in races against the clock, not racing up mountains.\", \"from\": 9460, \"to\": 9590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9499, \"end\": 9513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.649740716005446e-27, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his skill\", \"from\": 9525, \"to\": 9534}, {\"ngram\": \"races\", \"from\": 9541, \"to\": 9546}, {\"ngram\": \"the clock\", \"from\": 9555, \"to\": 9564}, {\"ngram\": \"mountains\", \"from\": 9580, \"to\": 9589}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Bradley Wiggins and Geraint Thomas, both Team GB athletes in recent years on the track, have won the Tour de France.\", \"from\": 9592, \"to\": 9717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9702, \"end\": 9716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.649740716005446e-27, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"recent years\", \"from\": 9662, \"to\": 9674}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 9678, \"to\": 9687}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both raced on the track to great success before refocussing on the road.\", \"from\": 9718, \"to\": 9790, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 9732, \"to\": 9741}, {\"ngram\": \"great success\", \"from\": 9745, \"to\": 9758}, {\"ngram\": \"the road\", \"from\": 9781, \"to\": 9789}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wiggins had a four-year gap, winning his last Olympic track medal in 2008 and the Tour de France in 2012.\", \"from\": 9791, \"to\": 9896, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wiggins\", \"from\": 9791, \"to\": 9798}, {\"ngram\": \"a four-year gap\", \"from\": 9803, \"to\": 9818}, {\"ngram\": \"his last Olympic track medal\", \"from\": 9828, \"to\": 9856}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas's gap was six years, winning in 2012 on the track and 2018 in France.\", \"from\": 9897, \"to\": 9973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9897, \"end\": 9903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.9936595283651348, \"rank\": 0.00638089799817388, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}, {\"begin\": 9966, \"end\": 9972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999995088729, \"rank\": 3.3545902683705176e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"six years\", \"from\": 9914, \"to\": 9923}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 9944, \"to\": 9953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite their mechanical simplicity, Olympic track bikes are very expensive.\", \"from\": 9977, \"to\": 10053, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their mechanical simplicity\", \"from\": 9985, \"to\": 10012}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic track bikes\", \"from\": 10014, \"to\": 10033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's due to the substantial R&D that goes into developing a top-fight track bike and the small market for Olympic-level track bikes.\", \"from\": 10054, \"to\": 10188, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the substantial R&D\", \"from\": 10068, \"to\": 10087}, {\"ngram\": \"a top-fight track bike\", \"from\": 10114, \"to\": 10136}, {\"ngram\": \"the small market\", \"from\": 10141, \"to\": 10157}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic-level track bikes\", \"from\": 10162, \"to\": 10187}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a constant arms race to make Olympic track bikes more aerodynamic and better performing.\", \"from\": 10189, \"to\": 10286, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a constant arms race\", \"from\": 10198, \"to\": 10218}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic track\", \"from\": 10227, \"to\": 10240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Team GB Hope-Lotus track bike frameset alone costs around \\u00a325,000, depending on the spec.\", \"from\": 10288, \"to\": 10381, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Team GB Hope-Lotus track bike frameset\", \"from\": 10288, \"to\": 10330}, {\"ngram\": \"the spec\", \"from\": 10372, \"to\": 10380}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The most expensive track bike is currently the Japanese V-Izu TCM-2, which costs over \\u00a3100,000 if you tried to buy one.\", \"from\": 10382, \"to\": 10501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10429, \"end\": 10437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9999998759385639, \"rank\": 1.2387540773934725e-07, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The most expensive track bike\", \"from\": 10382, \"to\": 10411}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most track riders have their bikes supplied by their national teams, so they are not paying for them.\", \"from\": 10502, \"to\": 10603, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Most track riders\", \"from\": 10502, \"to\": 10519}, {\"ngram\": \"their bikes\", \"from\": 10525, \"to\": 10536}, {\"ngram\": \"their national teams\", \"from\": 10549, \"to\": 10569}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's only recently that track bikes have become wide, with the Hope-Lotus bike the forerunner.\", \"from\": 10607, \"to\": 10701, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"track bikes\", \"from\": 10631, \"to\": 10642}, {\"ngram\": \"the Hope-Lotus bike\", \"from\": 10666, \"to\": 10685}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Previously, they were very narrow, but Team GB's research showed that the frame was more aerodynamic if the fork blades and seatstays were kept away from the turbulent air caused by the wheel and instead placed in line with the rider's legs.\", \"from\": 10702, \"to\": 10943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10741, \"end\": 10748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9995067483196731, \"rank\": 0.0004934943955907694, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the frame\", \"from\": 10772, \"to\": 10781}, {\"ngram\": \"the fork blades\", \"from\": 10806, \"to\": 10821}, {\"ngram\": \"seatstays\", \"from\": 10826, \"to\": 10835}, {\"ngram\": \"the turbulent air\", \"from\": 10856, \"to\": 10873}, {\"ngram\": \"the wheel\", \"from\": 10884, \"to\": 10893}, {\"ngram\": \"line\", \"from\": 10916, \"to\": 10920}, {\"ngram\": \"the rider's legs\", \"from\": 10926, \"to\": 10942}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a trend since adopted by other countries for their track bikes.\", \"from\": 10944, \"to\": 11012, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a trend\", \"from\": 10949, \"to\": 10956}, {\"ngram\": \"other countries\", \"from\": 10974, \"to\": 10989}, {\"ngram\": \"their track bikes\", \"from\": 10994, \"to\": 11011}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are other odd-looking aerodynamic features, such as the double seatpost on the French team's Look P24.\", \"from\": 11014, \"to\": 11122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11099, \"end\": 11105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6549877782810443, \"rank\": 0.5267460430104509, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other odd-looking aerodynamic features\", \"from\": 11024, \"to\": 11062}, {\"ngram\": \"the double seatpost\", \"from\": 11072, \"to\": 11091}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some track bikes have their drivetrains on the left, rather than the right side of the bike.\", \"from\": 11124, \"to\": 11216, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some track bikes\", \"from\": 11124, \"to\": 11140}, {\"ngram\": \"their drivetrains\", \"from\": 11146, \"to\": 11163}, {\"ngram\": \"the left\", \"from\": 11167, \"to\": 11175}, {\"ngram\": \"the right side\", \"from\": 11189, \"to\": 11203}, {\"ngram\": \"the bike\", \"from\": 11207, \"to\": 11215}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pioneered by the US team at the Rio games, the thinking is that since track bikes always turn to the left, the left side gearing is more sheltered by the front wheel and so more aerodynamic.\", \"from\": 11217, \"to\": 11407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11234, \"end\": 11236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"score\": 0.9997366692291173, \"rank\": 0.00026321058420407747, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\"}, {\"begin\": 11249, \"end\": 11252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.009040869366422e-17, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the thinking\", \"from\": 11260, \"to\": 11272}, {\"ngram\": \"track bikes\", \"from\": 11287, \"to\": 11298}, {\"ngram\": \"the left\", \"from\": 11314, \"to\": 11322}, {\"ngram\": \"the left side gearing\", \"from\": 11324, \"to\": 11345}, {\"ngram\": \"the front wheel\", \"from\": 11367, \"to\": 11382}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since they are ridden on the flat, there is no need for lower ratios to tackle hills.\", \"from\": 11409, \"to\": 11494, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no need\", \"from\": 11453, \"to\": 11460}, {\"ngram\": \"lower ratios\", \"from\": 11465, \"to\": 11477}, {\"ngram\": \"hills\", \"from\": 11488, \"to\": 11493}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Track riders train to deliver power efficiently at a range of cadences.\", \"from\": 11495, \"to\": 11566, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Track riders\", \"from\": 11495, \"to\": 11507}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 11525, \"to\": 11530}, {\"ngram\": \"a range\", \"from\": 11546, \"to\": 11553}, {\"ngram\": \"cadences\", \"from\": 11557, \"to\": 11565}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many track events only involve competition once the rider is moving, so there is little need for a low gear to get started either.\", \"from\": 11567, \"to\": 11697, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Many track events\", \"from\": 11567, \"to\": 11584}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 11598, \"to\": 11609}, {\"ngram\": \"the rider\", \"from\": 11615, \"to\": 11624}, {\"ngram\": \"little need\", \"from\": 11648, \"to\": 11659}, {\"ngram\": \"a low gear\", \"from\": 11664, \"to\": 11674}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Drafting occurs where a following rider rides close enough to the rider in front to benefit from their slipstream, thus saving a lot of energy - estimates range up to 50%.\", \"from\": 11699, \"to\": 11870, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Drafting\", \"from\": 11699, \"to\": 11707}, {\"ngram\": \"a following rider\", \"from\": 11721, \"to\": 11738}, {\"ngram\": \"the rider\", \"from\": 11761, \"to\": 11770}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 11774, \"to\": 11779}, {\"ngram\": \"their slipstream\", \"from\": 11796, \"to\": 11812}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 11826, \"to\": 11831}, {\"ngram\": \"energy - estimates\", \"from\": 11835, \"to\": 11853}, {\"ngram\": \"up to 50%\", \"from\": 11860, \"to\": 11869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a common tactic in all cycling, but particularly in track events such as the team pursuit, where riders will train to ride very close behind each other to maximise the aerodynamic gain.\", \"from\": 11872, \"to\": 12062, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a common tactic\", \"from\": 11877, \"to\": 11892}, {\"ngram\": \"all cycling\", \"from\": 11896, \"to\": 11907}, {\"ngram\": \"track events\", \"from\": 11929, \"to\": 11941}, {\"ngram\": \"the team pursuit\", \"from\": 11950, \"to\": 11966}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 11974, \"to\": 11980}, {\"ngram\": \"the aerodynamic gain\", \"from\": 12041, \"to\": 12061}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bikes designed for pursuit events, where riders keep up high speeds for longer distances, will be equipped with bar extensions.\", \"from\": 12064, \"to\": 12191, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bikes\", \"from\": 12064, \"to\": 12069}, {\"ngram\": \"pursuit events\", \"from\": 12083, \"to\": 12097}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 12105, \"to\": 12111}, {\"ngram\": \"high speeds\", \"from\": 12120, \"to\": 12131}, {\"ngram\": \"longer distances\", \"from\": 12136, \"to\": 12152}, {\"ngram\": \"bar extensions\", \"from\": 12176, \"to\": 12190}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once they have accelerated, when they will use the wider bars, riders will use the extensions.\", \"from\": 12192, \"to\": 12286, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wider bars\", \"from\": 12239, \"to\": 12253}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 12255, \"to\": 12261}, {\"ngram\": \"the extensions\", \"from\": 12271, \"to\": 12285}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These keep them low and tucked on the bike, for optimum aerodynamics.\", \"from\": 12287, \"to\": 12356, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bike\", \"from\": 12321, \"to\": 12329}, {\"ngram\": \"optimum aerodynamics\", \"from\": 12335, \"to\": 12355}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bikes used for sprints do not have extensions, since riders are putting in high effort for a shorter distance and so need to be able to pull against the handlebars, rather than getting tucked.\", \"from\": 12358, \"to\": 12550, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bikes\", \"from\": 12358, \"to\": 12363}, {\"ngram\": \"sprints\", \"from\": 12373, \"to\": 12380}, {\"ngram\": \"extensions\", \"from\": 12393, \"to\": 12403}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 12411, \"to\": 12417}, {\"ngram\": \"high effort\", \"from\": 12433, \"to\": 12444}, {\"ngram\": \"a shorter distance\", \"from\": 12449, \"to\": 12467}, {\"ngram\": \"the handlebars\", \"from\": 12507, \"to\": 12521}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A handsling is where one rider grabs another's hand behind them and pulls them forward.\", \"from\": 12552, \"to\": 12639, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A handsling\", \"from\": 12552, \"to\": 12563}, {\"ngram\": \"one rider\", \"from\": 12573, \"to\": 12582}, {\"ngram\": \"another's hand\", \"from\": 12589, \"to\": 12603}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a feature of the Madison event, where pairs of riders hand over racing between them, and allows the lead rider to impart their momentum to the follower, making for a faster handover.\", \"from\": 12640, \"to\": 12827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12662, \"end\": 12669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.915104069432535e-16, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a feature\", \"from\": 12645, \"to\": 12654}, {\"ngram\": \"pairs\", \"from\": 12683, \"to\": 12688}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 12692, \"to\": 12698}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead rider\", \"from\": 12741, \"to\": 12755}, {\"ngram\": \"their momentum\", \"from\": 12766, \"to\": 12780}, {\"ngram\": \"the follower\", \"from\": 12784, \"to\": 12796}, {\"ngram\": \"a faster handover\", \"from\": 12809, \"to\": 12826}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aerodynamics in track cycling extends from the design of bikes to the clothing worn.\", \"from\": 12829, \"to\": 12913, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Aerodynamics\", \"from\": 12829, \"to\": 12841}, {\"ngram\": \"track cycling\", \"from\": 12845, \"to\": 12858}, {\"ngram\": \"the design\", \"from\": 12872, \"to\": 12882}, {\"ngram\": \"bikes\", \"from\": 12886, \"to\": 12891}, {\"ngram\": \"the clothing\", \"from\": 12895, \"to\": 12907}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's been found that ridged fabrics can be more aerodynamic than smooth ones.\", \"from\": 12914, \"to\": 12991, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ridged fabrics\", \"from\": 12935, \"to\": 12949}, {\"ngram\": \"smooth ones\", \"from\": 12979, \"to\": 12990}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ridges and sawtooth trailing edges now extend to track bike frames too, in pursuit of optimum aerodynamics.\", \"from\": 12993, \"to\": 13100, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ridges\", \"from\": 12993, \"to\": 12999}, {\"ngram\": \"sawtooth trailing edges\", \"from\": 13004, \"to\": 13027}, {\"ngram\": \"bike frames\", \"from\": 13048, \"to\": 13059}, {\"ngram\": \"pursuit\", \"from\": 13068, \"to\": 13075}, {\"ngram\": \"optimum aerodynamics\", \"from\": 13079, \"to\": 13099}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A track stand is where a rider keeps their bike stationary by balancing their bike without putting a foot down.\", \"from\": 13102, \"to\": 13213, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A track stand\", \"from\": 13102, \"to\": 13115}, {\"ngram\": \"a rider\", \"from\": 13125, \"to\": 13132}, {\"ngram\": \"their bike\", \"from\": 13139, \"to\": 13149}, {\"ngram\": \"their bike\", \"from\": 13174, \"to\": 13184}, {\"ngram\": \"a foot\", \"from\": 13201, \"to\": 13207}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They may keep their bike completely stationary or, since the bike gearing is fixed, rock it slightly backwards and forwards.\", \"from\": 13214, \"to\": 13338, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their bike\", \"from\": 13228, \"to\": 13238}, {\"ngram\": \"the bike gearing\", \"from\": 13271, \"to\": 13287}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's used in individual sprint races to try to gain an advantage over an opponent and force them to lead out so that the second rider can slipstream them once the sprint phase starts.\", \"from\": 13340, \"to\": 13523, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"individual sprint races\", \"from\": 13353, \"to\": 13376}, {\"ngram\": \"an advantage\", \"from\": 13392, \"to\": 13404}, {\"ngram\": \"an opponent\", \"from\": 13410, \"to\": 13421}, {\"ngram\": \"the second rider\", \"from\": 13457, \"to\": 13473}, {\"ngram\": \"the sprint phase\", \"from\": 13499, \"to\": 13515}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On a typical Olympic length 250m track, the banking will rise to around 42 degrees.\", \"from\": 13525, \"to\": 13608, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a typical Olympic length\", \"from\": 13528, \"to\": 13552}, {\"ngram\": \"250m track\", \"from\": 13553, \"to\": 13563}, {\"ngram\": \"the banking\", \"from\": 13565, \"to\": 13576}, {\"ngram\": \"around 42 degrees\", \"from\": 13590, \"to\": 13607}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will be greater on a shorter track, and less on a longer track.\", \"from\": 13609, \"to\": 13675, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a shorter track\", \"from\": 13631, \"to\": 13646}, {\"ngram\": \"a longer track\", \"from\": 13660, \"to\": 13674}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As with all bikes used in competition, track bikes are subject to the UCI's 6.8kg minimum weight limit.\", \"from\": 13677, \"to\": 13780, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13747, \"end\": 13750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.154973793684369e-31, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all bikes\", \"from\": 13685, \"to\": 13694}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 13703, \"to\": 13714}, {\"ngram\": \"track bikes\", \"from\": 13716, \"to\": 13727}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since they are mechanically simple and usually built of carbon fibre, many will weigh around this value.\", \"from\": 13781, \"to\": 13885, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"carbon fibre\", \"from\": 13837, \"to\": 13849}, {\"ngram\": \"this value\", \"from\": 13874, \"to\": 13884}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Several nations are experimenting with 3D-printed metal track bike frames though, which may increase the weight somewhat.\", \"from\": 13887, \"to\": 14008, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Several nations\", \"from\": 13887, \"to\": 13902}, {\"ngram\": \"3D-printed metal track bike frames\", \"from\": 13926, \"to\": 13960}, {\"ngram\": \"the weight\", \"from\": 13988, \"to\": 13998}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A lot.\", \"from\": 14010, \"to\": 14016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A lot\", \"from\": 14010, \"to\": 14015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is avideoof German track cyclist Robert F\\u00f6rstemann generating enough power for over three minutes - around 700 watts - to toast a slice of bread.\", \"from\": 14017, \"to\": 14168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14035, \"end\": 14041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.9962714788944913, \"rank\": 0.003741113217848441, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 14056, \"end\": 14073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_F\\u00f6rstemann\", \"score\": 0.9999798197958497, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Robert F\\u00f6rstemann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_F\\u00f6rstemann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_F\\u00f6rstemann\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"enough power\", \"from\": 14085, \"to\": 14097}, {\"ngram\": \"over three minutes\", \"from\": 14102, \"to\": 14120}, {\"ngram\": \"around 700 watts\", \"from\": 14123, \"to\": 14139}, {\"ngram\": \"a slice\", \"from\": 14151, \"to\": 14158}, {\"ngram\": \"bread\", \"from\": 14162, \"to\": 14167}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In his prime, Chris Hoy could put out 2,500 watts and 700Nm torque.\", \"from\": 14169, \"to\": 14236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14183, \"end\": 14192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Hoy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his prime\", \"from\": 14172, \"to\": 14181}, {\"ngram\": \"2,500 watts\", \"from\": 14207, \"to\": 14218}, {\"ngram\": \"700Nm torque\", \"from\": 14223, \"to\": 14235}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A good benchmark for most male track sprinters is around 25 watts per kilo, and 20 watts per kilo for women.\", \"from\": 14237, \"to\": 14345, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A good benchmark\", \"from\": 14237, \"to\": 14253}, {\"ngram\": \"most male track sprinters\", \"from\": 14258, \"to\": 14283}, {\"ngram\": \"around 25 watts\", \"from\": 14287, \"to\": 14302}, {\"ngram\": \"kilo\", \"from\": 14307, \"to\": 14311}, {\"ngram\": \"20 watts\", \"from\": 14317, \"to\": 14325}, {\"ngram\": \"kilo\", \"from\": 14330, \"to\": 14334}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 14339, \"to\": 14344}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The black line, on the Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines Velodrome is measured at 250 metres (273.4 yards) long, as is Olympic standard.\", \"from\": 14347, \"to\": 14475, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The black line\", \"from\": 14347, \"to\": 14361}, {\"ngram\": \"the Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines Velodrome\", \"from\": 14366, \"to\": 14405}, {\"ngram\": \"250 metres\", \"from\": 14421, \"to\": 14431}, {\"ngram\": \"273.4 yards\", \"from\": 14433, \"to\": 14444}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic standard\", \"from\": 14458, \"to\": 14474}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The red line, which sits 90cm outward of the black line, is 5.7m longer for a full lap of the velodrome.\", \"from\": 14477, \"to\": 14581, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The red line\", \"from\": 14477, \"to\": 14489}, {\"ngram\": \"the black line\", \"from\": 14518, \"to\": 14532}, {\"ngram\": \"a full lap\", \"from\": 14553, \"to\": 14563}, {\"ngram\": \"the velodrome\", \"from\": 14567, \"to\": 14580}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the very inside edge of the track is a flat section.\", \"from\": 14583, \"to\": 14638, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the very inside edge\", \"from\": 14586, \"to\": 14606}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 14610, \"to\": 14619}, {\"ngram\": \"a flat section\", \"from\": 14623, \"to\": 14637}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Usually unboarded and made of concrete, it's used to get started.\", \"from\": 14639, \"to\": 14704, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"concrete\", \"from\": 14669, \"to\": 14677}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Next is a light blue line, dubbed the 'C\\u00f4te d'Azur', which indicates the inside edge of the track.\", \"from\": 14706, \"to\": 14804, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a light blue line\", \"from\": 14714, \"to\": 14731}, {\"ngram\": \"the 'C\\u00f4te d'Azur\", \"from\": 14740, \"to\": 14756}, {\"ngram\": \"the inside edge\", \"from\": 14775, \"to\": 14790}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 14794, \"to\": 14803}]}, {\"sentence\": \"20cm above this is a black line, which denotes the length of the track and is followed as much as possible by riders to keep the distance they have to travel to a minimum.\", \"from\": 14805, \"to\": 14976, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a black line\", \"from\": 14824, \"to\": 14836}, {\"ngram\": \"the length\", \"from\": 14852, \"to\": 14862}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 14866, \"to\": 14875}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 14915, \"to\": 14921}, {\"ngram\": \"the distance\", \"from\": 14930, \"to\": 14942}, {\"ngram\": \"a minimum\", \"from\": 14966, \"to\": 14975}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 90cm above the black line is a red line.\", \"from\": 14978, \"to\": 15021, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the black line\", \"from\": 14992, \"to\": 15006}, {\"ngram\": \"a red line\", \"from\": 15010, \"to\": 15020}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Called the sprinter's line, it's used in sprint competitions.\", \"from\": 15022, \"to\": 15083, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sprinter's line\", \"from\": 15029, \"to\": 15048}, {\"ngram\": \"sprint competitions\", \"from\": 15063, \"to\": 15082}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As long as a lead rider is between the black and red lines, another rider must pass above them.\", \"from\": 15084, \"to\": 15179, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lead rider\", \"from\": 15095, \"to\": 15107}, {\"ngram\": \"the black and red lines\", \"from\": 15119, \"to\": 15142}, {\"ngram\": \"another rider\", \"from\": 15144, \"to\": 15157}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While being passed, the leader can not move above the red line and must stay within the two lines.\", \"from\": 15180, \"to\": 15278, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the leader\", \"from\": 15200, \"to\": 15210}, {\"ngram\": \"the red line\", \"from\": 15230, \"to\": 15242}, {\"ngram\": \"the two lines\", \"from\": 15264, \"to\": 15277}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, there is a blue line further up the track, which is used in the Madison.\", \"from\": 15280, \"to\": 15361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15353, \"end\": 15360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.915104069432535e-16, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a blue line\", \"from\": 15298, \"to\": 15309}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 15321, \"to\": 15330}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Every not-in-play rider from each pairing must remain above this so that they are not in the way of competing riders.\", \"from\": 15362, \"to\": 15479, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"play\", \"from\": 15375, \"to\": 15379}, {\"ngram\": \"each pairing\", \"from\": 15391, \"to\": 15403}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 15451, \"to\": 15458}, {\"ngram\": \"competing riders\", \"from\": 15462, \"to\": 15478}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both are part of the same group.\", \"from\": 15481, \"to\": 15513, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 15490, \"to\": 15494}, {\"ngram\": \"the same group\", \"from\": 15498, \"to\": 15512}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As with many performance motor sport brands, such as Red Bull and McLaren, Lotus Group includes an engineering consultancy, which developed the Hope-Lotus bike alongside British Cycling.\", \"from\": 15514, \"to\": 15700, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15580, \"end\": 15587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McLaren\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8639244707540014e-23, \"text\": \"McLaren\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McLaren\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McLaren\"}, {\"begin\": 15589, \"end\": 15594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lotus_Cars\", \"score\": 0.9999995175877556, \"rank\": 4.824123872217071e-07, \"text\": \"Lotus\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lotus_Cars\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lotus_Cars\"}, {\"begin\": 15684, \"end\": 15699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many performance motor sport brands\", \"from\": 15522, \"to\": 15557}, {\"ngram\": \"Red Bull\", \"from\": 15567, \"to\": 15575}, {\"ngram\": \"an engineering consultancy\", \"from\": 15610, \"to\": 15636}, {\"ngram\": \"the Hope-Lotus bike\", \"from\": 15654, \"to\": 15673}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hope Tech is a cycling brand primarily focused on mountain bikes and components, which is responsible for building the frameset.\", \"from\": 15702, \"to\": 15830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15702, \"end\": 15706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hope\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.209062636076165e-15, \"text\": \"Hope\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hope\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hope\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a cycling brand\", \"from\": 15715, \"to\": 15730}, {\"ngram\": \"mountain bikes\", \"from\": 15752, \"to\": 15766}, {\"ngram\": \"components\", \"from\": 15771, \"to\": 15781}, {\"ngram\": \"the frameset\", \"from\": 15817, \"to\": 15829}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As with their bikes and clothing, aero is everything for track cyclists.\", \"from\": 15832, \"to\": 15904, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their bikes\", \"from\": 15840, \"to\": 15851}, {\"ngram\": \"clothing\", \"from\": 15856, \"to\": 15864}, {\"ngram\": \"aero\", \"from\": 15866, \"to\": 15870}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 15874, \"to\": 15884}, {\"ngram\": \"track cyclists\", \"from\": 15889, \"to\": 15903}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An enclosed helmet with a long tail and a visor will be more aerodynamic than a standard vented road helmet.\", \"from\": 15905, \"to\": 16013, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An enclosed helmet\", \"from\": 15905, \"to\": 15923}, {\"ngram\": \"a long tail\", \"from\": 15929, \"to\": 15940}, {\"ngram\": \"a visor\", \"from\": 15945, \"to\": 15952}, {\"ngram\": \"a standard vented road helmet\", \"from\": 15983, \"to\": 16012}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When cycling, one of the biggest obstacles that cyclists have to overcome is the air.\", \"from\": 16015, \"to\": 16100, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"When cycling\", \"from\": 16015, \"to\": 16027}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest obstacles\", \"from\": 16036, \"to\": 16057}, {\"ngram\": \"cyclists\", \"from\": 16063, \"to\": 16071}, {\"ngram\": \"the air\", \"from\": 16092, \"to\": 16099}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's for this reason that aerodynamic bikes, helmets and clothing is so highly sought after, and riders often go to altitude for world record attempts.\", \"from\": 16101, \"to\": 16252, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this reason\", \"from\": 16110, \"to\": 16121}, {\"ngram\": \"aerodynamic bikes\", \"from\": 16127, \"to\": 16144}, {\"ngram\": \"helmets\", \"from\": 16146, \"to\": 16153}, {\"ngram\": \"clothing\", \"from\": 16158, \"to\": 16166}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 16198, \"to\": 16204}, {\"ngram\": \"altitude\", \"from\": 16217, \"to\": 16225}, {\"ngram\": \"world record attempts\", \"from\": 16230, \"to\": 16251}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The higher the air density, the more air they have to push out of the way, and that takes more power.\", \"from\": 16254, \"to\": 16355, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The higher the air density\", \"from\": 16254, \"to\": 16280}, {\"ngram\": \"the more air\", \"from\": 16282, \"to\": 16294}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 16320, \"to\": 16327}, {\"ngram\": \"more power\", \"from\": 16344, \"to\": 16354}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lower air density means there is less air to overcome, which requires less power, or equals faster speeds for an equivalent power.\", \"from\": 16356, \"to\": 16486, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Lower air density\", \"from\": 16356, \"to\": 16373}, {\"ngram\": \"less air\", \"from\": 16389, \"to\": 16397}, {\"ngram\": \"less power\", \"from\": 16426, \"to\": 16436}, {\"ngram\": \"faster speeds\", \"from\": 16448, \"to\": 16461}, {\"ngram\": \"an equivalent power\", \"from\": 16466, \"to\": 16485}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a thunderstorm, air pressure is significantly reduced, which means low air pressure, less resistance to overcome, in turn higher speeds, and therefore faster times!\", \"from\": 16488, \"to\": 16658, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a thunderstorm\", \"from\": 16494, \"to\": 16508}, {\"ngram\": \"air pressure\", \"from\": 16510, \"to\": 16522}, {\"ngram\": \"low air pressure\", \"from\": 16561, \"to\": 16577}, {\"ngram\": \"turn\", \"from\": 16611, \"to\": 16615}, {\"ngram\": \"higher speeds\", \"from\": 16616, \"to\": 16629}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Inside the velodrome it is hot, and while riding body temperatures can rocket which has a detrimental impact on performance.\", \"from\": 16660, \"to\": 16784, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the velodrome\", \"from\": 16667, \"to\": 16680}, {\"ngram\": \"body temperatures\", \"from\": 16709, \"to\": 16726}, {\"ngram\": \"a detrimental impact\", \"from\": 16748, \"to\": 16768}, {\"ngram\": \"performance\", \"from\": 16772, \"to\": 16783}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In order to counteract this, riders will warm up while wearing vest filled with cooling gel.\", \"from\": 16785, \"to\": 16877, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 16788, \"to\": 16793}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 16814, \"to\": 16820}, {\"ngram\": \"gel\", \"from\": 16873, \"to\": 16876}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This loosens up the muscles while keeping core temperatures from getting too high.\", \"from\": 16878, \"to\": 16960, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the muscles\", \"from\": 16894, \"to\": 16905}, {\"ngram\": \"core temperatures\", \"from\": 16920, \"to\": 16937}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paul has been on two wheels since he was in his teens and he's spent much of the time since writing about bikes and the associated tech.\", \"from\": 16962, \"to\": 17098, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Paul\", \"from\": 16962, \"to\": 16966}, {\"ngram\": \"two wheels\", \"from\": 16979, \"to\": 16989}, {\"ngram\": \"his teens\", \"from\": 17006, \"to\": 17015}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 17039, \"to\": 17047}, {\"ngram\": \"bikes\", \"from\": 17068, \"to\": 17073}, {\"ngram\": \"the associated tech\", \"from\": 17078, \"to\": 17097}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's a road cyclist at heart but his adventurous curiosity means Paul has been riding gravel since well before it was cool, adapting his cyclo-cross bike to ride all-day off-road epics and putting road kit to the ultimate test along the way.\", \"from\": 17099, \"to\": 17340, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a road cyclist\", \"from\": 17104, \"to\": 17118}, {\"ngram\": \"heart\", \"from\": 17122, \"to\": 17127}, {\"ngram\": \"his adventurous curiosity\", \"from\": 17132, \"to\": 17157}, {\"ngram\": \"Paul\", \"from\": 17164, \"to\": 17168}, {\"ngram\": \"gravel\", \"from\": 17185, \"to\": 17191}, {\"ngram\": \"his cyclo-cross bike\", \"from\": 17232, \"to\": 17252}, {\"ngram\": \"road\", \"from\": 17273, \"to\": 17277}, {\"ngram\": \"road kit\", \"from\": 17296, \"to\": 17304}, {\"ngram\": \"the ultimate test\", \"from\": 17308, \"to\": 17325}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 17332, \"to\": 17339}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paul has contributed to Cyclingnews' tech coverage for a few years, helping to maintain the freshness of our buying guides and deals content, as well as writing a number of our voucher code pages.\", \"from\": 17341, \"to\": 17537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17365, \"end\": 17376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cyclingnews\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Paul\", \"from\": 17341, \"to\": 17345}, {\"ngram\": \"a few years\", \"from\": 17396, \"to\": 17407}, {\"ngram\": \"the freshness\", \"from\": 17429, \"to\": 17442}, {\"ngram\": \"our buying guides\", \"from\": 17446, \"to\": 17463}, {\"ngram\": \"deals\", \"from\": 17468, \"to\": 17473}, {\"ngram\": \"content\", \"from\": 17474, \"to\": 17481}, {\"ngram\": \"a number\", \"from\": 17502, \"to\": 17510}, {\"ngram\": \"our voucher code pages\", \"from\": 17514, \"to\": 17536}]}, {\